title: FDIC Chairman Jelena McWilliams Resigns
sub_head: Resignation follows public fight with Democratic board members over control of FDIC board
body:
Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. Chairman Jelena McWilliams resigned on Friday, the agency said.
Ms. McWilliams, a Trump administration holdover, had fought publicly with Democrats who now make up a majority of the FDIC board over control of the agencyâ€™s policy agenda.
